Nigerian-American radio presenter, Dan Foster has died.
Although details of his death is still sketchy, a source said that the veteran radio host died around 1pm on Wednesday. According to the source who declined anonymity, “he died today around 1pm. His wife is currently at the isolation centre in Yaba as we speak.” While the cause of his death is yet to be confirmed — as of the time this report was filed — immediate suspicion is that he died of COVID-19, the respiratory disease caused by coronavirus. Prior to his demise, Foster worked with Cool FM, Inspiration FM , City FM and Classic FM.  Click Here>>>>>>Anti-kidnap and anti-theft device for tracking and listening<<<<<< 